Appendix A — Data Model & Database Schema Outline (PostgreSQL)
Version: v1.0   Date: 2025-12-20
This appendix defines an MVP-ready schema that scales to multi-supplier, mixed fulfillment, invoicing, and returns.
A1) Design Principles (Non-Negotiable)
Canonical product model in our DB. Supplier feeds never become the runtime “source of truth.”
Keep supplier data separate (raw snapshots + mappings) to allow audit, rollback, and multi-supplier scaling.
Order data immutable once paid (except status transitions). Never recalculate totals after payment.
Use strong IDs and timestamps everywhere; use UUID for public entities to avoid enumeration.
Events & jobs are first-class: async imports, invoices, emails, tracking updates.
Tax/price snapshots must be stored per order item at purchase time.

