A3) Critical Indexes (Performance)
products(slug) unique
skus(sku_code) unique
categories(slug) unique
brands(slug) unique
orders(order_number) unique
orders(customer_id, created_at desc)
order_items(order_id)
supplier_products(supplier_id, supplier_sku) unique
supplier_stock(updated_at)
sku_attributes(attribute_id, value_number) and sku_attributes(attribute_id, attribute_value_id)
Consider full-text index on products.title + products.description_html (or use OpenSearch)

A4) Notes on Search and Filters
For PCComponentes-like filtering: keep attributes normalized for fast filtering.
Use a search index (OpenSearch/Algolia) with: product title, brand, categories, key specs flattened, price and availability.
DB remains the source of truth; search index is derived.

A5) Multi-Supplier Roadmap (Built Into Schema)
Schema supports supplier mapping via supplier_products and linking to skus.
For multi-supplier per SKU, add: sku_supplier_links(sku_id, supplier_product_id, priority, is_preferred).
Supplier selection can be: lowest landed cost + availability + SLA policy.

A6) MVP “Minimum Set” (If Time Is Tight)
Keep: products, skus, categories, brands.
Keep: supplier_products, supplier_stock, supplier_prices.
Keep: orders, order_items, payments, invoices.
Keep: shipments.
Keep: jobs (mandatory).
Everything else can be Phase 2.

